# Mobile Design System Enforcement

When editing mobile UI, apply `.claude/skills/autocare-design-system/SKILL.md`.

## Non-negotiable constraints

- Preserve one clear visual focal point per screen.
- Keep explicit action hierarchy (primary vs secondary).
- Use consistent spacing/radius/type rhythm.
- Prefer tokenized styles and shared UI primitives over inline ad-hoc styling.
- No hardcoded user-facing strings in JSX; use i18n keys.
- No hardcoded color literals when token classes exist.

## Review gate before finishing

- Can the screen hierarchy be understood in 3 seconds?
- Do loading/empty/error states keep the same visual language?
- Is there any duplicated heading or structural noise?
- Are related pieces grouped in cards/sections instead of loose text?
